This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a gathering to honor the 35th anniversary of the terrorist attack on the Marine Barracks in Beirut, Lebanon. The President pays tribute to the 241 American service members who lost their lives in the attack and expresses gratitude to the families of the fallen heroes. He also discusses the fight against terrorism and highlights the actions taken against Iran and Hezbollah. The President emphasizes the strength and commitment of the US military and vows to use all necessary resources to confront terrorism. He concludes by thanking the Gold Star families for their service and sacrifice.